The appeal of this album isn&#039;t limited to children--though the gentle repertoire 
and soft acoustic musical accompaniment will surely soothe little ones at the 
end of a long day, adults will find the silky-smooth vocals, beautiful 
harmonies, and creative production just as engaging. Parents will enjoy 
listening to the metamorphosis of Loggins&#039;s 1969 Top 40 hit "House on Pooh 
Corner" to the updated &#039;90s version. And with titles like the traditional "All the 
Pretty Little Ponies" and "To-Ra-Loo-Ra" and covers of Paul Williams&#039;s 
"Rainbow Connection," Jimmy Webb&#039;s "The Last Unicorn," and John Lennon&#039;s 
"Love," Mom might find herself borrowing this CD from the nursery when it 
comes time to kick back and relax after the kids are asleep. --Deborah Moore
